A circumscribing  \alpha-pseudocircle are circular arcs with endpoints at the vertices of the polygon which all lie inside the circumscribing circle of the polygon and make an angle at most \alpha with the circumscribing polygon at the verticies. A pseudocircle is \alpha-empty if it is an \alpha-pseudocircle and it contains no verticies in its interior.
